OL,3,CSex offence anonymity law ruled
OL,4,C'incompatible with press freedom'
OL,6,FThe verdict represents victory for
OL,7,Fmedia organisations including the
OL,8,FBelfast Telegraph and Irish News who
OL,9,Fchallenged legislation that prohibits
OL,10,Fthe naming of alleged perpetrators
OL,11,Fbefore they have been charged or until
OL,12,F25 years after their death.
OL,14,FMr Justice Humphreys found that the
OL,15,Frelevant sections of the Justice
OL,16,F(Sexual Offences and Trafficking
OL,17,FVictims) Act (Northern Ireland) 2022
OL,18,Fare "not law" and failed to strike a
OL,19,Ffair balance between suspects rights
OL,20,Fto privacy and press freedom.
