OL,3,CSex offence anonymity law ruled
OL,4,C'incompatible with press freedom'
OL,6,FIn proceedings against Stormont's
OL,7,FDepartment of Justice, conflicting
OL,8,Frights to privacy and freedom of
OL,9,Fexpression protected by Articles 8 and
OL,10,F10 of the European Convention on Human
OL,11,FRights (ECHR) came under scrutiny.
OL,13,FIt was contended that victims of sex
OL,14,Fcrimes in Northern Ireland could face
OL,15,Fsix months in prison if they publicly
OL,16,Fname their suspected abusers.
OL,18,FMeanwhile, alleged perpetrators would
OL,19,Falso unfairly remain protected from
OL,20,Fidentification for up to 25 years
OL,21,Fafter their death.
